messages.content: You are tasked with creating a structured output from the provided user message.

- Full path: /admin/useed

- all HTTP methods acceptable: false

- HEAD: false
- POST: true
- OPTIONS: false
- TRACE: false
- GET: false
- PUT: false
- DELETE: false
- PATCH: false

Explanation:
- The AdminController class has no class-level @RequestMapping, so method-level mappings are the full paths.
- The useed() method is annotated with @RequestMapping(value = "/admin/useed", method = RequestMethod.POST). That explicitly maps only POST requests to the path "/admin/useed".
- Because the method attribute is RequestMethod.POST, no other HTTP methods (including HEAD, GET, OPTIONS, TRACE, PUT, DELETE, PATCH) are declared acceptable by the code. I based the answers strictly on the source annotations (not on framework runtime behaviors like automatic OPTIONS handling).
